President Biden met with President Yoon Suk Yeol of South Korea in Seoul. They both reiterated their commitment to strengthening the alliance between the US and South Korea and expanding its focus beyond the Korean Peninsula to address global challenges. They discussed increasing cooperation on critical technologies, economic and energy security, global health, and climate change. The leaders also emphasized the importance of constitutional democracy, individual rights, and regional security. They pledged to strengthen deterrence and cooperate closely on addressing the threat from North Korea. They also expressed concerns about the spread of COVID-19 in North Korea and expressed support for international assistance.